<h1 id="install" class="step">Install Tails using <i>GNOME Disks</i></h1>

<div class="step-image">[[!img inc/infography/install-tails.png link="no" alt=""]]</div>

1. Install *GNOME Disks*.

   - If you are using the GNOME desktop environment,
     *GNOME Disks* should be installed by
     default.

   - Otherwise, install the `gnome-disk-utility`
     package using the usual installation method for your distribution.

     You can also install Tails using the
     `dd` command from any Linux distribution
     as described in our instructions for [[installing from Debian using
     the command line|install/expert#install]].

